programme.title: The Masters
programme.desc: Action from the fourth day from the Augusta National in Georgia, as the opening Major of 2016 reached a conclusion. Jordan Speith started the final day four shots ahead of his nearest rival last year and showed no signs of any nerves affecting his game, eventually holding that advantage ahead of Phil Mickelson and Justin Rose, who were tied for second. Speith also equalled the lowest 72-hole total for the Masters and set the record for the most birdies for the week.(n)

programme.desc: AT&T Pebble Beach Pro-Am final-round play from California's famed Pebble Beach Golf Links. Jordan Spieth won by four shots last year at 20-under-par, en route to a three-win season. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Genesis Open
programme.desc: Genesis Open final-round play from Riviera CC in Pacific Palisades, Cal. Dustin Johnson (17-under-par) rolled to victory last year by five shots over Scott Brown and Thomas Pieters. Tiger Woods returned to the field this week, last appearing in 2006. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Honda Classic
programme.desc: Honda Classic final-round play from PGA National (Champion Course) in Palm Beach Gardens, Fla. Rickie Fowler shot 12-under-par in taking last year's title by four shots over Morgan Hoffmann and Gary Woodland. It was Fowler's fourth Tour victory. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: WGC-Mexico Championship
programme.desc: World Golf Championships-Mexico Championship final-round play from Club de Golf Chapultepec in Mexico City. Dustin Johnson won here at 14-under-par last year, one shot better than England's Tommy Fleetwood. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Valspar Championship
programme.desc: Valspar Championship final-round play from Innisbrook Resort (Copperhead course) in Palm Harbor, Fla. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Arnold Palmer Invitational
programme.desc: Arnold Palmer Invitational final-round play from Bay Hill Club & Lodge in Orlando, Fla. Last year, Marc Leishman (11-under-par) became the fourth-straight winner here to prevail by one shot. There has not been a playoff since 1999. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: WGC-Dell Technologies Match Play
programme.desc: World Golf Championships-Dell Technologies Match Play finals and third-place match from Austin CC in Texas. Dustin Johnson edged Spain's Jon Rahm 1-up last year to become the first player with wins in all four WGC events. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Corales Puntacana Resort & Club Championship
programme.desc: Corales Puntacana Resort & Club Championship final-round play in the Dominican Republic. This former Web.com Tour event has a purse of $3 million. Six holes play along the ocean, with the 18th hole requiring a carry over the cliff-lined Bay of Corales. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Houston Open
programme.desc: Houston Open final-round play from the Golf Club of Houston in Humble, Texas. Last year, Russell Henley racked up 10 birdies in a final-round 65 to win at 20-under-par, three shots better than Sung Kang. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: RBC Heritage
programme.desc: Final-round play in the RBC Heritage in Hilton Head Island, S.C. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Valero Texas Open
programme.desc: Valero Texas Open final-round play from TPC San Antonio. Kevin Chappell (12-under-par) broke into the PGA Tour winner's circle for the first time in this event last year, nipping Brooks Koepka by one shot in a Monday finish. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Zurich Classic of New Orleans
programme.desc: Zurich Classic of New Orleans final-round play from TPC Louisiana in Avondale. Alternate-shot play concludes this two-man team event, won last year by Jonas Blixt and Cameron Smith (27-under-par) after four playoff holes vs. Kevin Kisner and Scott Brown. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Wells Fargo Championship
programme.desc: Wells Fargo Championship final-round play from Quail Hollow Club in Charlotte, N.C. Last year, Brian Harman became the 12th American winner in this event's 15 years, with Rory McIlroy (2010, 2015) and Vijay Singh (2005) claiming the other wins. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: The Players Championship
programme.desc: The Players Championship final-round play from TPC Sawgrass in Ponte Vedra Beach, Fla. South Korea's Si Woo Kim won this unofficial "fifth major" last year at 10-under-par, and was one of just two top-10 finishers to break 70 in the final round. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: AT&T Byron Nelson
programme.desc: AT&T Byron Nelson final-round play from Trinity Forest GC in Dallas. This new links-style layout (designed by Bill Coore and Ben Crenshaw) is the event's 11th different venue. Features include a double green for holes 3 and 11; and the 630-yard 14th. (cc).(n)

programme.title: PGA Tour Golf: Fort Worth Invitational
programme.desc: Fort Worth Invitational final-round play from Colonial CC in Texas. (cc).(n)
